  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Humane Management of Mixed Migration Flows in Zimbabwe through the Provision of Life-Saving Assistance and Protection of Migrants&#x2019; Dignity and Rights, in Order to Build Resilience and Strengthen Social Cohesion.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The unpredictable and critical nature of Zimbabwe has reinforced the need for IOM to continue conducting data collection through Protection information management tools as the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) to provide information on the location and multisectoral needs of the affected population particularly returnees to the humanitarian partners for a more targeted response, since most of them remain dependent on humanitarian assistance. The focus of this intervention is mainly at Border level and will be achieved by continuing the provision of services for the main points of entry (POEs) of the country (Beitbridge, Plumtree and Chirundu), while extending services to a key POE (Forbes). In addition, the action proposes to continue strengthening the capacity of Government to properly manage migration flows, while improving the existing coordination mechanisms and providing the resources required to guarantee the protection of vulnerable migrants, in terms of the life-threatening challenges related to the spread of COVID-19 and tackling vulnerabilities by challenging discrimination and inequalities.</narrative>
  </description>
